    <stitle>FRAME - MXT - DRILLING - HOLE LOCATION GUIDELINES</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="x0100102" svcproctype="install" graphiccount="2">
        <title>HOLE LOCATION GUIDELINES</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Never drill holes into the restricted areas of the frame rails. Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0100108">Figure 12</hotlnk>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use existing holes whenever possible.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Maintain a minimum of 0.75 inch (19 mm) of material between holes.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">There should not be more than three holes located on a vertical line.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Bolt holes should be no larger than is required for the size of bolts being used, in no
                instance larger than 11/16 (.688 inch).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If reinforcements are used, avoid drilling holes closer than 2.0 inches (51 mm) from the
                ends of the reinforcement.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Bolts must be periodically checked to insure that the proper torque and clamping force is
                maintained.
            </para>
        </step1>
